on a large set of case studies attending to the consequences of energy change processes so as to make these consequences explicit to actors. The chapter then explains how the book addresses the current conduct of the energy transition by inquiring into its key dimensions, namely making new energy resources, passing through markets, economic instruments, technological demonstration, and the spatialities and temporalities of energy transition processes.\"\n                    data-doc-authors=\"Olivier Labussiere, Alain Nada√Ø (2018)\"\n                    data-doc-year=\"2018\"\n                    onmouseover=\"showTooltip(event, this)\"\n                    onmouseout=\"hideTooltip()\">\n                    How to inquire about energy transition processes?\n                </h4>\n                <p class=\"document-authors\">Olivier Labussiere, Alain Nada√Ø (2018)</p>\n                <p class=\"document-links\">\n            <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-77025-3_1\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 flex items-center\">\n                <span class=\"mr-1\">üîó</span>\n                DOI: 10.1007/978-3-319-77025-3_1\n            </a>\n        \n            <a href=\"https://hal.science/halshs-01675679\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 flex items-center\">\n                <span class=\"mr-1\">üîó</span>\n                HALId: halshs-01675679\n            </a>\n        </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n        </div>\n    "
